{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":91948,"duration_api_ms":160305,"num_turns":6,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"f405a027-ccec-469f-a9ce-f267486a27a9","total_cost_usd":0.4629749999999999,"usage":{"input_tokens":864,"cache_creation_input_tokens":26967,"cache_read_input_tokens":79891,"output_tokens":2647,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":26967,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":212,"outputTokens":9971,"cacheReadInputTokens":792050,"cacheCreationInputTokens":43775,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.18399075,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":864,"outputTokens":2647,"cacheReadInputTokens":79891,"cacheCreationInputTokens":26967,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.27898425,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"Verified all 5 amendments against the source code in src/adapters/process_backend.rs and src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs. Four amendments identify confirmed real defects (conditional compilation, process group isolation, background reap asymmetry, artifact preservation). One amendment (fr-20-abd81d04) correctly self-resolves as safe after analysis — preserve_interrupted_run unconditionally overwrites interrupted_run, so the .take() consumption is harmless.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-20-8020c938","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified: the classify_exit_tests module at line 2954 imports std::os::unix::process::ExitStatusExt unconditionally (line 2957), with no #[cfg(unix)] on the module. The production classify_exit_failure function properly gates the same import inside a #[cfg(unix)] block (lines 1505-1514). This is a real compilation failure on non-Unix targets. Adding #[cfg(unix)] to the test module is the correct minimal fix."},{"amendment_id":"fr-20-abd81d04","decision":"reject","rationale":"Verified safe. The amendment itself concludes 'No change needed if confirmed' and I confirm. preserve_interrupted_run (lines 579-581) unconditionally executes snapshot.interrupted_run = snapshot.active_run.clone(). After line 4711 restores active_run via interrupted_run.take(), active_run is valid. If the cancellation check at line 4714 fires, fail_run_result → fail_run → preserve_interrupted_run overwrites interrupted_run with the now-valid active_run.clone(). The prior .take() having consumed interrupted_run is irrelevant because preserve_interrupted_run writes unconditionally. No code change warranted."},{"amendment_id":"fr-20-34e3c3b6","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified: Command::new at lines 985-992 spawns with default process group — no setsid(), pre_exec(), or process_group() call anywhere in the file. All kill paths (force_kill, send_sigkill, confirm_teardown) target only the direct child PID. If the backend command spawns subprocesses, those descendants inherit stdout/stderr but are not in a killable process group. On timeout, only the direct child is killed; descendants leak and survive into subsequent retries. This is a real process lifecycle defect that violates the acceptance criterion for killing hanging backend processes."},{"amendment_id":"fr-20-7c859012","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified asymmetry: the cancel path (lines 1380-1390) calls spawn_background_reap() when the grace period expires, ensuring a slow-to-die child is eventually force-killed and waited on in a detached task. The timeout path (lines 1062-1088) calls remove_child_if_same() and returns immediately when confirm_teardown returns false — no background reap is spawned. A child that survives the 2-second teardown grace period becomes completely untracked: no Arc<ManagedChild> reference remains, no reaper task runs, and future cancel/retry operations cannot find it. The fix should mirror the cancel path by spawning a background reap when teardown is not confirmed."},{"amendment_id":"fr-20-92204543","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified: at lines 1068-1075, unconfirmed teardown is intentionally downgraded from Timeout to TransportFailure. At lines 1259-1266, invoke() only preserves failed artifacts (schema_path, message_path) when failure_class() == Timeout; all other failures including TransportFailure trigger prepared.cleanup() which calls best_effort_cleanup() (lines 1539-1544) to delete the temp files. This creates an ironic diagnostic gap: the hardest timeout failures to debug — where the process could not even be confirmed killed — are exactly the ones whose diagnostic artifacts are deleted. The fix should preserve artifacts for TransportFailure originating from timeout paths, or separate the failure class downgrade from artifact-preservation decisions."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"675b2599-9bf1-4665-ae31-a6f273e7f83a"}
